  <div id="exchange_options" class="get_smly_section">
    <div class="get_smly_section_info_text">
      <h2> 3. Buy SMLY at a cryptocurrency exchange </h2>
      <p> Getting into the world of cryptocurrencies is a bit tricky. There are several hurdles to get started using cryptocoins and buying your first SMLY is not quite trivial. </p>

      <p> You will always need to have an account at a cryptocurrency exchange. </p>

      <p> The exchanges at <a href="https://tradesatoshi.com/">Tradesatoshi</a>, <a href="https://www.southxchange.com/Market/Book/SMLY/DOGE">SouthXchange</a> and <a href="https://p2pb2b.io/">p2pb2b</a> have several "markets", i.e. places which look like a stock market and you can sell one cryptocurrency for another. These exchanges have several SMLY markets. </p>

      <p> Before entering any of these exchanges to buy SMLY, however, you need to convert fiat money (USD, ISK, EUR) to Bitcoin or another cryptocurrency first. This is most commonly done on a national exchange such as <a href="https://isx.is/">isx.is</a> </p>

      <p> Alternatively you can use a broker who handles the entire process, such as <a href="http://balkar.is/">Bálkar Miðlun</a>. </p>
    </div>
